
Overview of noun reward

The noun reward has 5 senses (first 4 from tagged texts)
                                         
1. (4) wages, reward, payoff -- (a recompense for worthy acts or retribution for wrongdoing; "the wages of sin is death"; "virtue is its own reward")
2. (2) reward -- (payment made in return for a service rendered)
3. (2) reward, reinforcement -- (an act performed to strengthen approved behavior)
4. (1) reward -- (the offer of money for helping to find a criminal or for returning lost property)
5. advantage, reward -- (benefit resulting from some event or action; "it turned out to my advantage"; "reaping the rewards of generosity")

Overview of verb reward

The verb reward has 3 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                         
1. (1) honor, honour, reward -- (bestow honor or rewards upon; "Today we honor our soldiers"; "The scout was rewarded for courageous action")
2. (1) reinforce, reward -- (strengthen and support with rewards; "Let's reinforce good behavior")
3. reward, repay, pay back -- (act or give recompense in recognition of someone's behavior or actions)
